President Biden met virtually with G20 Leaders to discuss Afghanistan. They discussed the need to focus on counterterrorism efforts, particularly against threats from ISIS-K, and ensuring safe passage for foreign nationals and Afghan partners seeking to leave Afghanistan. They also reaffirmed their commitment to providing humanitarian assistance and promoting human rights for all Afghans, including women, girls, and minority groups. The United States is committed to working with the international community to address the situation in Afghanistan and support the Afghan people.